author: Nick Hallett
title: Britain’s Population Will Be Bigger than France within 13 Years
text: Shoppers out in London's Oxford street looking for bargains as sales start early Thursday, Dec., 23, 2010. Britain is battered by economic woes, and the shopping season was shortened by bad weather, so the final hopes of rescuing the retail season rest on last minute shoppers, predominantly men who are desperate to find a credible gift before it's finally, utterly, too late. This pressure is expected to bring record number of nervous, credit-card-ready consumers into Britain's malls and shops Thursday night as retailers predict the most intense shopping binge of the year.(AP Photo/Alastair Grant)
